#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Find the Smallest Divisor Given a Threshold (Binary Search on Answer)

Is question mein hume smallest divisor find karna hai
aisa ki array ke har element ko us divisor se divide karke
un sabka ceil value ka sum threshold se chhota ya equal ho.

Brute force mein hum har divisor try kar sakte hain,
lekin range badi ho sakti hai,
isliye Binary Search on Answer use karenge.

Key Idea:
Divisor ki range:
minimum divisor = 1
maximum divisor = max(nums)

Agar divisor chhota hoga,
to division ke baad values badi aayengi,
aur total sum bhi zyada hoga.

Agar divisor bada hoga,
to division ke baad values chhoti aayengi,
aur total sum kam hoga.

Matlab:
Jaise-jaise divisor badhega, total sum ghatta jayega.
Yeh monotonic behavior hai,
isliye binary search lag sakti hai.

How helper works:
Har element ke liye:
ceil(nums[i] / mid)

Fir sabka sum nikalte hain.

Example:
nums[i] = 7, divisor = 3
ceil(7/3) = 3

nums[i] = 10, divisor = 2
ceil(10/2) = 5

Agar total sum <= threshold hai,
to current divisor valid hai.
Lekin hume smallest valid divisor chahiye,
isliye left side search karenge.

Agar total sum > threshold hai,
to divisor chhota hai,
hume divisor bada karna padega.
Isliye right side search karenge.

Steps:
1. low = 1, high = maximum element in array
2. mid = (low + high) / 2
3. helper se total sum nikalo using ceil(nums[i] / mid)
4. Agar sum <= threshold
   -> divisor valid hai
   -> smaller divisor dhoondo
   -> high = mid - 1
5. Else
   -> divisor small hai
   -> bada divisor chahiye
   -> low = mid + 1

Loop ke end par low smallest valid divisor hota hai.

Why return low?
Kyuki binary search ke baad low first aisa divisor hota hai
jiske liye total sum threshold ke andar aa jata hai.

Time Complexity:
maxi() -> O(n)
helper() -> O(n)
Binary Search -> O(log(max element))
Total -> O(n * log(max element))

Space Complexity:
O(1)

One line intuition:
Aisa smallest divisor find karna hai jisse ceil divisions ka total sum threshold ke andar aa jaye,
isliye answer space par binary search lagate hain.

#Code:

class Solution {

    public int maxi(int[] nums){
        int n = nums.length;
        int maxVal = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            maxVal = Math.max(maxVal, nums[i]);
        }
        return maxVal;
    }

    public int helper(int[] nums, int mid){
        int sum = 0;
        int n = nums.length;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            sum += Math.ceil((double)nums[i] / mid);
        }
        return sum;
    }

    public int smallestDivisor(int[] nums, int threshold) {
        int low = 1;
        int high = maxi(nums);

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low+high)/2;
            int val = helper(nums, mid);

            if(val <= threshold){
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else{
                low = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return low;
    }
}
